1 convincing the National Farm Workers Association (NFWA), a
2 primarily Mexican-American farmworkers union led by Cesar
3 Chavez, to join forces with the AWOC; and
4 WHEREAS, Garnering national attention, the Delano Grape
5 Strike resulted in the first union contracts for farmworkers, which
6 included improved wages, benefits and working conditions, and
7 transformed the farm labor movement in the United States through
8 its use of boycotts, the groundbreaking collaboration between
9 farmworkers of Filipino and Mexican heritage and the formation of
10 the United Farm Workers labor union from the merger of the
11 AWOC and the NFWA; and
12 WHEREAS, Known as a father of the West Coast labor
13 movement, Larry Itliong was a tireless labor organizer, community
14 leader and activist for social and economic justice; and
15 WHEREAS, Larry Itliong’s legacy is a source of pride for
16 Filipino-Americans, who constitute the largest segment of the
17 Asian-American, Native Hawaiian and Pacific Islander population,
18 which is the fastest growing demographic group in the State of
19 Nevada and the United States; and
20 WHEREAS, The State of Nevada desires to recognize the many
21 contributions Larry Itliong made to the State of Nevada and the
22 United States; now, therefore,
23
24 THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
25 SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
26
27 Section 1. Chapter 236 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
28 thereto a new section to read as follows:
29 1. The Governor shall annually proclaim October 25 to be
30 “Larry Itliong Day” in the State of Nevada.
31 2. The proclamation must call upon the news media,
32 educators, business and labor leaders and appropriate
33 governmental officers to bring to the attention of the residents of
34 Nevada the important contributions Larry Itliong made to the
35 State of Nevada and the United States.
36 Sec. 2. This act becomes effective upon passage and approval.
